<HEADLINE>
FT  11 SEP 93 / Markets: Deadline for BES investors - At a glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Business Expansion Scheme investors who did not use up their full Pounds
40,000 allowance in the 1992-93 tax year have only until October 5 to carry
back tax relief. The maximum that can be carried back to offset against last
year's liability, is 50 per cent of their BES investment in the current tax
year to a maximum of Pounds 5,000. If you have invested only Pounds 8,000
before October 5, Pounds 4,000 can be carried back but if you have invested
Pounds 30,000, you can carry back only Pounds 5,000. More BES, page VII.
</TEXT>
