FT  11 SEP 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Black pepper prices advanced further, reports Man Producten, as replacement
levels continued to climb. And there was more demand for decorticating black
into white. White pepper prices stabilised at high levels. European stocks
have dwindled as demand from the US has intensified. White: Muntok/Sarawak
faq for September/October delivery was quoted at Dollars 3,900 a tonne, with
spot supplies at Dollars 4,000. Black: Sarawak black label spot was Dollars
1,950 a tonne and for September/October Dollars 1,925. Yellow label spot was
Dollars 2,075a tonne, and September/October Dollars 2,000. Brazilian grade 1
spot was offered at Dollars 1,950 a tonne.
