essential for the political and economic wellbeing of Nigeria, and anything
that will disrupt the peace should therefore be avoided.'
Mr Abiola, regarded as the winner of a June 12 presidential election
annulled by former military ruler General Ibrahim Babangida, has been abroad
mobilising support for his claim to the presidency.
