FT  11 SEP 93 / Fake World Bank securities
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT PESTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Financial fraudsters have been trying to sell hundreds of millions of
dollars of fake World Bank securities in the US and the UK, writes Robert
Peston. The World Bank, the multilateral development bank, yesterday warned
investors not to buy prime bank notes or prime bank guarantees which carry
its name.
Investors are offered astonishingly high rates of interest. A scheme being
marketed in the UK offers 156 per cent return for an investment of Dollars
10m (Pounds 6.4m) and 260 per cent for Dollars 100m and higher.
