FT  10 SEP 93 / Deutsche Aerospace Airbus announces job cuts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ARIANE GENILLARD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Deutsche Aerospace Airbus, the German aircraft manufacturer, announced
yesterday that it will cut up to 2,800 jobs by the end of 1995 in nine to 10
factories across Germany, writes Ariane Genillard in Bonn.
The company said the 'dramatic' decline in the demand for aircraft had
forced it to cut its workforce of 20,600 by 13 per cent.
The company, which is a subsidiary of Deutsche Aerospace, itself owned by
Daimler-Benz, reported profits of DM410.8m (Dollars 253.5m) in 1992, down
from DM421.3m the previous year.
