FT  10 SEP 93 / International Company News: Record earnings for Campbell
Soup
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By FRANK MCGURTY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CAMPBELL Soup, the US food products group, said yesterday it had achieved
record earnings and sales in the fourth quarter, buoyed by a strong
contribution from overseas markets.
Earnings and revenues for the full year also reached record levels for the
fourth consecutive time.
The results highlight Campbell's recent efforts to reorganise its global
operations, as well as its renewed emphasis on its core soup, biscuits and
bakery businesses.
Net earnings in the quarter to August 1 were 11 per cent higher at Dollars
122m, or 48 cents a share, up from Dollars 109m, or 44 cents. Revenues rose
7 per cent from Dollars 1.4bn to Dollars 1.5bn.
Before the cumulative effect of accounting changes, earnings in the 1993
quarter were 15 per cent up.
For the full year, net earnings before special charges rose by almost 17 per
cent to Dollars 574m, or Dollars 2.28 a share.
