FT  10 SEP 93 / UK Company News: All-round growth at British Dredging
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Progress all round coupled with much higher net margins enabled British
Dredging to raise pre-tax profits by 28 per cent from Pounds 578,000 to
Pounds 739,000 in the first half of 1993.
Turnover of the building materials, ship repairing and concrete products
group, rose only 7 per cent to Pounds 17.35m. Mr Fane Vernon, chairman, said
this increase was entirely due to the full six months' contribution from the
604 builders merchants business which was acquired in March 1992 and from
Selco's Cardiff branch - opened in July 1992.
Operating profits grew 83 per cent to Pounds 655,000. Net interest received
was lower at Pounds 84,000 (Pounds 306,000) because of the group's
investment in new branches of JT Edwards and Selco Trade Centres and reduced
interest rates.
Last time there was also an exceptional charge of Pounds 85,000. Earnings
per share increased from 2.2p to 2.83p, while an unchanged interim dividend
of 2.6p is declared.
